00:17:23.860 --> 00:17:26.860
Oh. There was something back in the first grade.

00:17:26.860 --> 00:17:30.860
Thank you! It's more than I've uncovered in like the past two days. Now please, let's continue.

00:17:30.859 --> 00:17:35.859
There was this bully three grades ahead of us. This dude was determined to pound Denson to every kid in the school.

00:17:35.859 --> 00:17:39.859
One day I guess it was my turn. He was just about to take my head off when Clark jumped between us.

00:17:39.859 --> 00:17:41.859
So Clark ran interference.

00:17:43.859 --> 00:17:47.859
Now as kind as that sounds, Preet, I really don't think it falls under the something amazing test.

00:17:47.859 --> 00:17:51.859
What test? I'm not finished. Clark didn't just push Braindead away.

00:17:51.859 --> 00:17:55.859
He put him through a door, as in splinters and broken hinges. How he did it, I still have no idea.

00:17:55.859 --> 00:17:57.859
